						<summary>

						<p>Slab lying outside the Pañchaliṅga cave.</p>						

						<p>This is dated [Śaka 1363], Durmati, Pushya ba ...</p>						

						<p>Damaged. Seems to register a gift of land to the god Pañchaliṅga-siddhayya made into the hands of Nāgadēvayya, son of Jaṅgama Saṅgamanātha, for the merit of <hi rend="italic">Mahāmaṇḍalēśvara</hi> Vallabhaya and his son Timmayya.</p>						

